The paper introduces a new dataset for traditional Chinese machine reading comprehension (MRC), which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions building a baseline model using deep learning techniques, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the dataset involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language understanding (NLU), which could make cs.IR and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) relevant sub-categories as well.
